<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limonia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Limonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized in the family by the following features: body color from yellow to gray, brown or black; medium-sized (body length 5.3-12.1 mm, wing length 5.4-13.2 mm); first thoracic segment elongate; episternum setose; tarsal claw with three to five teeth; wing wide with well-developed anal angle, pattern ranging from completely transparent or patternless to smoky or with dotted markings; Sc1 apically reaching from base of Rs to branching point of Rs; Sc2 close to apex of Sc1; terminal section of R1 continuing direction of R1 and longer than R2 (often at least two times longer than R2); discal cell closed; basal deflection of CuA1 at or slightly before branching point of M; male genitalia with wide ninth tergite slightly emarginate at posterior margin; gonocoxite with wide but often low ventromesal lobe; gonostylus single, situated apically, wider at base, narrowed and slightly arched at apex; aedeagus simple, elongate with bifid apex that is turned into the ventral margin; paramere wide at base; cercus of female terminalia slightly turned upwards (
<bibRefCitation author="Savchenko, EN" journalOrPublisher="Fauna Ukrainy" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 180" refId="B17" refString="Savchenko, EN, 1985. Komary-limoniidy [limoniid-flies]. Subfamily Limoniinae. Fauna Ukrainy 14 (4): 1 - 180" title="Komary-limoniidy [limoniid-flies]. Subfamily Limoniinae." volume="14" year="1985">Savchenko 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Reusch, H" editor="Nilsson, A" journalOrPublisher="2). Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="105 - 132" refId="B16" refString="Reusch, H, Oosterbroek, P, 1997. Diptera Limoniidae and Pediciidae, Short-palped Crane Flies. In: Nilsson, A, Ed., Aquatic Insects of North Europe (Vol. 2). Stenstrup: 105 - 132" title="Diptera Limoniidae and Pediciidae, Short-palped Crane Flies." volumeTitle="Aquatic Insects of North Europe (Vol." year="1997">Reusch and Oosterbroek 1997</bibRefCitation>
; Stary and Salmela 2004; 
